returns._0: True if all votes are cast, false otherwise.

proposalDeadline(address,uint256).details: Gets the deadline timestamp for voting on a specified proposal.

params.governor: The governor contract that manages the proposal.
params.proposalId: The unique identifier for the proposal.

returns.deadline: The timestamp by which votes for the proposal need to be submitted.

proposalSnapshot(address,uint256).details: Retrieves the snapshot timestamp of a given proposal.

params.governor: The governor contract that manages the proposal.
params.proposalId: The unique identifier for the proposal in question.

returns.snapshot: The timestamp at which the voting snapshot for the proposal was taken.

proxyVotingDeadline(address,uint256).details: Calculates the deadline for proxy voting on a particular proposal.      The proxy voting deadline is set at 80% of the full voting window to ensure      that proxy votes are cast before the final voting deadline.

params.governor: The governor contract that oversees the proposal.
params.proposalId: The unique identifier for the proposal.

returns.proxyDeadline: The timestamp by which proxy votes for the proposal must be submitted.

startCastingVotes(address,uint256).details: Initiates the process of casting aggregated votes for a specified proposal.      This function validates that the function call is made after 80% of the full      voting window has elapsed, providing a buffer period before the actual      voting deadline.

params.governor: The governor contract that manages the proposal.
params.proposalId: The unique identifier for the proposal.

areAllVotesCast(address,uint256).notice: Checks if all votes have been cast for a proposal.

continueCastingVotes(address,uint256).notice: Continues the process of casting votes for a given proposal.
